The Azure Free Account is designed to help new users explore Azure services at no initial cost. It includes free access to popular services for 12 months, limited free tier services that are always free, and a credit (typically $200) for the first 30 days.

This allows users to experiment with cloud services without financial risk.

For example, a beginner learning cloud computing can deploy a small web app, experiment with storage services, and monitor usage—all within the free tier limits.

A startup can also use the free account to prototype applications before committing to a paid plan. For instance, testing an API backend using Azure Functions and Cosmos DB.

However, users must monitor usage carefully because exceeding free limits can result in charges.
